        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 3:34PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 334 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Leader, or 25 miles southwest of Fort Morgan, moving northeast at 5
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hoyt, Leader, Adena, Twelve-Mile Corner and Hoyt Beet Dump.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rain is occurring with this storm and may lead to flooding. Do
not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
